summary: Game of Thrones - 'The Last of the Starks' Review
title: Game of Thrones - 'The Last of the Starks' Review
description:
“We may have defeated them, but there’s still us to contend with.”

Previously, I’d written reviews for a couple of different episodes centered around epic battles. In this case, I felt fortunate to be reviewing an episode that’s all about the aftermath of an epic battle, as well as a prelude for the next one.

summary: It would have been really nice to have a scene with Dany interacting with Ghost.  I mean, Jon got to bond with/ride Rhaegal and...
body:
It would have been really nice to have a scene with Dany interacting with Ghost.  I mean, Jon got to bond with/ride Rhaegal and even almost petted Drogon, but you couldn’t have one scene with Dany bonding with Ghost?

But that’s right, I forgot: that would get in way of the Starks hating Dany.  Sheesh…
